changes.value:
kanban-app/ui/src/lib/refresh.test.ts:4,8

```ts
const mockInvoke = vi.fn((..._args: any[]) => Promise.resolve({}));
// ...
vi.mock("@tauri-apps/api/core", () => ({
  invoke: (...args: any[]) => mockInvoke(...args),
}));
```

Both usages carry an `// eslint-disable-next-line @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` comment, signalling awareness, but the JS/TS guidelines require `unknown` over `any`. In test files this is low risk, but it sets a bad precedent.

Suggestion: Change the mock signatures to use `unknown[]`:
```ts
const mockInvoke = vi.fn((..._args: unknown[]) => Promise.resolve({}));
```"

